0.text: Well Seymour, I made it despite your directions.

1.text: Ah Superintendent Chalmers, welcome. I hope you're prepared for an unforgettable luncheon.

3.text: So ye gods, my roast is ruined.

4.text: But what if I were to purchase fast food and disguise it as my own cooking?

5.text: Ho ho ho ho ho, delightfully devilish Seymour.

6.text: Skinner with his crazy explanations, the Superintendent's gonna need his medication.

7.text: When he hears Skinner's lame exaggerations, there'll be trouble in town tonight.

9.text: Superintendent, I was just stretching my calves on the windowsill. Isometric exercise. Care to join me?

10.text: Why is there smoke coming out of your oven Seymour?

11.text: Oh that isn't smoke, it's steam. Steam from the steamed clams we're having. Mmmmm steamed clams.

12.text: Superintendent, I hope you're ready for mouth-watering hamburgers.

13.text: I thought we were having steamed clams.

14.text: Oh no, I said steamed hams. That's what I call hamburgers.

19.text: Really? Well I'm from Utica and I've never heard anyone use the phrase steamed hams.

20.text: Oh not in Utica, no, it's an Albany expression.

22.text: You know these hamburgers are quite similar to the ones they have at Krusty Burger.

23.text: Ho ho ho ho, no, patented Skinner Burger's old family recipe.

26.text: And you call them steamed hams despite the fact they are obviously grilled.

27.text: You know, one thing I should... excuse me for one second.

29.text: Oh well that was wonderful. Good time was had by all. I'm pooped.

30.text: Yes I should be... Good Lord what is happening in there?

32.text: Uh, Aurora Borealis. At this time of year, at this time of day, in this part of the country, localized entirely within your kitchen.

36.text: Seymour, the house is on fire!

37.text: No mother, it's just the northern lights.

38.text: Well Seymour, you are an odd fellow, but I must say, you steam a good ham.
